RNA-Seq Analysis SRP022028 Revision

Trent Gutierrez

2022-09-27

Introduction

Research question

This RNA-Seq analysis looks at data from iPSCs derived from patients of 22q11.2 deletion syndrome and how it affects neuronal development and activity pathways. 22q11.2 DS is one of the highest known risk factors for developing schizophrenia (SZ) and research has been limited due to the fact that analyzing developing human brains is inaccessible, thats where Induced Pluripotent Stem Cells (iPSC) come in, they help give researchers a opportunity to grow patient-specific neurons in vitro, and these cells can have the abnormalities needed for the investigation. The data for this analysis will be 8 samples of 14 day old neurons, where 4 are from SZ patients (2 confirmed 22q11.2 DS samples, 2 uncertain patient samples) and 4 controls of normal neurons.
